# API Design Standards

## Purpose
Keep APIs typed, predictable, and easy to evolve.

## Requirements
- define clear endpoint names and responsibilities
- make request and response shapes explicit
- validate all incoming external data
- use a consistent error structure
- keep controllers thin and service logic separate
- do not expose storage or query-layer details in public responses
- keep authentication and authorization checks near the boundary
- design for predictable pagination, filtering, and failure behavior
- document contract changes before implementation when they affect other layers

## Apply When
- creating or changing endpoints
- defining DTOs and validation
- adjusting controller/service boundaries
